</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tori-shima, the largest of the uninhabited islands, had a population of 150 until 1902, when all were killed by a volcanic eruption. Since then, the island has been uninhabited.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Administrative_divisions">Administrative divisions</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Izu_Islands&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Administrative divisions">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The Izu Islands are divided into two towns (Oshima and Hachijojima) and six villages (remaining inhabited islands.)  Three <a href="/wiki/Subprefectures_of_Japan" title="Subprefectures of Japan">subprefectures</a> are formed above the municipalities as branch offices of the <a href="/wiki/Tokyo_Metropolitan_Government" title="Tokyo Metropolitan Government">metropolitan government</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Favro-Brebbia_2-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Favro-Brebbia-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>All the islands (more than a dozen in total) lie within the <a href="/wiki/Fuji-Hakone-Izu_National_Park" title="Fuji-Hakone-Izu National Park">Fuji-Hakone-Izu National Park</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Favro-Brebbia_2-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Favro-Brebbia-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The four southernmost islands are not administrated under any town or village in Hachijō Subprefecture, but are <a href="/wiki/Unincorporated_area" title="Unincorporated area">unincorporated areas</a>.  <a href="/wiki/Torishima_(Izu_Islands)" class="mw-redirect" title="Torishima (Izu Islands)">Torishima</a> is now uninhabited but is an important bird refuge.
</p><p>Deserted islands between Aogashima and Ogasawara Islands, namely Bayonaise Rocks (<i>Beyonēzu Retsugan</i>), <a href="/wiki/Smith_Island_(Japan)" title="Smith Island (Japan)">Smith Island</a> (<i>Sumisu-tō</i>), <a href="/wiki/Torishima_(Izu_Islands)" class="mw-redirect" title="Torishima (Izu Islands)">Torishima</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Lot%27s_Wife_(crag)" title="Lot&#39;s Wife (crag)">Lot's Wife</a> (<i>Sōfu-iwa</i>) do not belong to any <a href="/wiki/Municipalities_of_Japan" title="Municipalities of Japan">municipality</a>, because both Hachijō Town and Aogashima Village claim administrative rights. They are directly controlled by <a href="/wiki/Hachij%C5%8D_Subprefecture" title="Hachijō Subprefecture">Hachijō Subprefecture</a> instead.
</p>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/%C5%8Cshima_Subprefecture_(Tokyo)" title="Ōshima Subprefecture (Tokyo)">Ōshima Subprefecture</a>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/File:Flag_of_Oshima,_Tokyo.svg" class="image"><img alt="Flag of Oshima, Tokyo.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Flag_of_Oshima%2C_Tokyo.svg/22px-Flag_of_Oshima%2C_Tokyo.svg.png" decoding="async" width="22" height="15" class="thumbborder" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Flag_of_Oshima%2C_Tokyo.svg/33px-Flag_of_Oshima%2C_Tokyo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Flag_of_Oshima%2C_Tokyo.svg/44px-Flag_of_Oshima%2C_Tokyo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="900" data-file-height="600" /></a> <a href="/wiki/%C5%8Cshima,_Tokyo" title="Ōshima, Tokyo">Ōshima</a> Town: <a href="/wiki/Izu_%C5%8Cshima" title="Izu Ōshima">Izu Ōshima</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Toshima,_Tokyo_(village)" class="mw-redirect" title="Toshima, Tokyo (village)">Toshima</a> Village: <a href="/wiki/Toshima_Island" class="mw-redirect" title="Toshima Island">Toshima</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Niijima,_Tokyo" title="Niijima, Tokyo">Niijima</a> Village: <a href="/wiki/Niijima" class="mw-redirect" title="Niijima">Niijima</a>, <a href="/wiki/Shikinejima" class="mw-redirect" title="Shikinejima">Shikinejima</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Udoneshima" class="mw-redirect" title="Udoneshima">Udoneshima</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/K%C5%8Dzushima,_Tokyo" title="Kōzushima, Tokyo">Kōzushima</a> Village: <a href="/wiki/K%C5%8Dzushima" class="mw-redirect" title="Kōzushima">Kōzushima</a></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Miyake_Subprefecture" title="Miyake Subprefecture">Miyake Subprefecture</a>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Miyake,_Tokyo" title="Miyake, Tokyo">Miyake</a> Village: <a href="/wiki/Miyakejima" class="mw-redirect" title="Miyakejima">Miyakejima</a> and <a href="/wiki/%C5%8Cnoharajima" class="mw-redirect" title="Ōnoharajima">Ōnoharajima</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Mikurajima,_Tokyo" title="Mikurajima, Tokyo">Mikurajima</a> Village: <a href="/wiki/Mikurajima" class="mw-redirect" title="Mikurajima">Mikurajima</a>, <a href="/wiki/Inambajima" class="mw-redirect" title="Inambajima">Inambajima</a></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hachij%C5%8D_Subprefecture" title="Hachijō Subprefecture">Hachijō Subprefecture</a>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/File:Flag_of_Hachijo,_Tokyo.svg" class="image"><img alt="Flag of Hachijo, Tokyo.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Flag_of_Hachijo%2C_Tokyo.svg/22px-Flag_of_Hachijo%2C_Tokyo.svg.png" decoding="async" width="22" height="15" class="thumbborder" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Flag_of_Hachijo%2C_Tokyo.svg/33px-Flag_of_Hachijo%2C_Tokyo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Flag_of_Hachijo%2C_Tokyo.svg/44px-Flag_of_Hachijo%2C_Tokyo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="900" data-file-height="600" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Hachij%C5%8D,_Tokyo" title="Hachijō, Tokyo">Hachijō</a> Town: <a href="/wiki/Hachij%C5%8Djima" class="mw-redirect" title="Hachijōjima">Hachijōjima</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hachij%C5%8Dkojima" class="mw-redirect" title="Hachijōkojima">Hachijōkojima</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/File:Flag_of_Aogashima,_Tokyo.svg" class="image"><img alt="Flag of Aogashima, Tokyo.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Flag_of_Aogashima%2C_Tokyo.svg/22px-Flag_of_Aogashima%2C_Tokyo.svg.png" decoding="async" width="22" height="15" class="thumbborder" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Flag_of_Aogashima%2C_Tokyo.svg/33px-Flag_of_Aogashima%2C_Tokyo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Flag_of_Aogashima%2C_Tokyo.svg/44px-Flag_of_Aogashima%2C_Tokyo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="900" data-file-height="600" /></a> <a href="/wiki/Aogashima,_Tokyo" title="Aogashima, Tokyo">Aogashima</a> Village: <a href="/wiki/Aogashima" title="Aogashima">Aogashima</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Unincorporated_area" title="Unincorporated area">unincorporated</a>: <a href="/wiki/Bayonnaise_Rocks" title="Bayonnaise Rocks">Bayonnaise Rocks</a> (<i>Beyonēzu Retsugan</i>), <a href="/wiki/Smith_Island_(Japan)" title="Smith Island (Japan)">Sumisu-tō</a>, <a href="/wiki/Torishima_(Izu_Islands)" class="mw-redirect" title="Torishima (Izu Islands)">Torishima</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Lot%27s_Wife_(crag)" title="Lot&#39;s Wife (crag)">Sōfu-iwa</a></li></ul></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Demographics">Demographics</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Izu_Islands&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Demographics">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Though the population on the Izu Islands has been dropping, the phase is less dramatic than on other isolated Japanese islands.<sup id="cite_ref-Favro-Brebbia_2-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Favro-Brebbia-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<table class="wikitable sortable">
<caption>Population changes<sup id="cite_ref-Favro-Brebbia_2-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Favro-Brebbia-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</caption>
<tbody><tr>
